target:
 Measuring tree diameter at breast height (dbh)

If necessary, here's a simple Python function to calculate the dbh from the given text:

```python
def calculate_dbh(text):
    if "diameter at breast height" in text:
        start = text.index("diameter at breast height")
        end = text.index("\n", start)
        return float(text[start + len("diameter at breast height"):end].strip().replace(",", "."))
    else:
        return None
```

This function calculates and returns the dbh value in meters from the input text, assuming it follows the given format.
